{"session_id":"svc-1778087875144662234","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-06T17:17:57.301788781Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","work_dir":"/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-f326f001-20260506T171752-9eaf51c0","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260506T171752-9eaf51c0/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260506T171752-9eaf51c0/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If you write `.ddx/executions/20260506T171752-9eaf51c0/no_changes_rationale.txt`, it MUST carry one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;one-line shell command\u0026gt;` — the loop runs it (cwd = project root, 60s); exit 0 closes the bead, non-zero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: needs_investigation` + `reason: \u0026lt;why\u0026gt;` — bead stays open for triage.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Bare rationales (\u0026#34;nothing to do\u0026#34;) are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260506T171752-9eaf51c0/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260506T171752-9eaf51c0/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Bead overrides project defaults\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead description and AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and conservative project defaults (YAGNI, DOWITYTD, no-docs-unless-asked) in this worktree — write whatever the bead asks for.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Decomposition depth cap\u0026#xA;This bead is already at decomposition depth 3. Do not create another child layer; if it is still too large, reject the split with a short explanation and write no_changes_rationale.txt instead.\u0026#xA;\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-f326f001\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003ework: render terminal result lines with status-specific markers\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;`ddx work` prints a success-looking terminal line for failed iterations. Operators see output such as `✓ ddx-8fa7ecf6 → error: pre-close review: review-error: transport`, where the leading checkmark contradicts the error detail and makes it unclear whether the bead closed successfully.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;`cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:1214-1215` always prints `✓ \u0026lt;bead\u0026gt; → \u0026lt;formatted-result\u0026gt;` whenever an iteration finishes, regardless of `ExecuteBeadReport.Status`. `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:1590-1616` formats failed statuses as `error: ...`, but the caller still prefixes them with the success glyph.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- Add a small terminal result-line formatter near `formatLoopResult` that returns both a status marker and the existing concise result text.\u0026#xA;- Use a success marker only for `success` and `already_satisfied` results.\u0026#xA;- Use a neutral or failure marker for `no_changes`, review malfunction, execution_failed, post-run check failures, and other non-closing statuses so the first token no longer implies success.\u0026#xA;- Keep persisted `bead.result` events and status enums unchanged; this bead is CLI/log presentation only.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Renaming `pre-claim intake` / `pre-dispatch lint` readiness-hook terminology; that is owned by `ddx-1c0de0af`.\u0026#xA;- Review retry/manual-required policy; that is owned by `ddx-639af4ef` and related review beads.\u0026#xA;- Changing status taxonomy or persisted event schemas; classification work is owned by `ddx-e2479b81`.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. `TestFormatLoopResultLine_SuccessUsesSuccessMarker` proves success and already_satisfied statuses render with the success marker and unchanged concise result text.\u0026#xA;2. `TestFormatLoopResultLine_FailuresDoNotUseSuccessMarker` proves review malfunction, execution_failed, post_run_check_failed, no_evidence_produced, and preserved-error statuses do not render with `✓`.\u0026#xA;3. `TestExecuteBeadLoop_LogLineDoesNotUseSuccessMarkerForReviewError` covers a loop result with `Detail=\u0026#34;pre-close review: review-error: transport\u0026#34;` and asserts the emitted log line does not start with `✓`.\u0026#xA;4. Existing `formatLoopResult` behavior remains covered for `merged`, `already_satisfied`, `no_changes`, `preserved: ...`, and `error: ...` text.\u0026#xA;5. `cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... -run \u0026#34;TestFormatLoopResult|TestExecuteBeadLoop_LogLine\u0026#34; -count=1` passes.\u0026#xA;6. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, area:agent, area:cli, kind:bug, reliability, operator-ux, spec:FEAT-010\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-a9d130d0\" spec-id=\"FEAT-010\" base-rev=\"e2306cff5c2d6941cd54ee303ddd00169418d5a1\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260506T171752-9eaf51c0\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"FEAT-010\" path=\"docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-010-task-execution.md\"\u003eFeature: Task Execution\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"attempt_id":"20260506T171752-9eaf51c0","base_rev":"e2306cff5c2d6941cd54ee303ddd00169418d5a1","bead_id":"ddx-f326f001","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260506T171752-9eaf51c0","correlation_id":"ddx-f326f001:20260506T171752-9eaf51c0","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260506T171752-9eaf51c0/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"391224c510a0893a0e68ca236569d0ca529cc715bffb129624fee4a4350f0858","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-b4115df5","worker_id":""}}}
